sec.p:
The algorithm used to find common targets of let7-c, miR128 and miR125b is provided below.use strict;
my $targets1= @ARGV[0]; 
my $targets2= @ARGV[1]; 
my $outfile="Overlap_".$targets1.$targets2;
my %ref;
open IN, "<$targets1" or die $!;
while (<IN>){
   if (/(NM_\d+)/){
      $ref{$1}=$_;
   }
}
my $i=0;
open IN2, "<$targets2" or die $!;
open OUT, ">$outfile" or die $!;
while (<IN2>){
   if (/(NM_\d+)/){
      my $ID=$1;
      my $match=$ref{$ID};
      if (defined $match){
         $i++;
         print OUT "$ID\n";
      }
   }
}
print " NUmber of overlaps between $targets1 and $targets2 is $i\n";
